Title   : ​Gainers & Losers: Urban Company, Vedanta among 8 stocks that hogged limelight on Wednesday 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-17T10:59:46
Fetched : 2025-09-17T12:07:41.115469
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/gainers-losers-urban-company-vedanta-among-8-stocks-that-hogged-limelight-on-wednesday/slideshow/123943480.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Sep 17, 2025
Indian headline indices continued their winning momentum on Wednesday led by gains in auto, IT and bank stocks. The Nifty ended at 25,330, gaining by 91 points or 0.36% while the BSE Sensex closed at 82,69, rising 31 points or 0.38%. Here are the stocks that saw action today:
Image Source: iStock
Shares of Multi Commodity Exchange of India (MCX) rallied 5% intraday before closing 4% higher at Rs 7,923. The stock rallied after Sebi Chairman Tuhin Kanta Pandey signaled fresh measures to deepen India’s commodity markets. Reuters quoted Pandey saying that the regulator plans to work with the government to allow banks and pension funds to trade in commodities as part of its broader agenda to deepen the market.
Image Source: iStock
Shares of Urban Company settled 4% at Rs 169 higher after making a stellar debut on BSE, NSE today. The stock listed at a 57% premium on the BSE over its issue price of Rs 103.
Image Source: iStock
Shares of Garden Reach Shipbuilders & Engineers (GRSE) shot up 6.4% to close the day at Rs 2,595.20 amid strong traction for most defence stocks during the session. The stock also broke its two-session losing streak.
Image Source: iStock
Shares of State Bank of India (SBI) rallied 3% to settle close the day at Rs 856.90 on the NSE after the state-lender completed divestment of its 13.19% stake in Yes Bank for a consideration of Rs 8,889 crore.
Image Source: iStock
Shares of Shringar House of Mangalsutra listed at a 14% premium at Rs 187.70 on the NSE over the issue price of Rs 165. However, the stock gave up some of its listing gains during the session to settle at Rs 187, down by Rs 1.50 or 0.80%.
Image Source: iStock
Metal major Vedanta's shares fell nearly 4% intraday to hit the day's low of Rs 471 after its demerger plans received another setback with the government doubling down on its objection, claiming that the demerged scheme proposed is being used as a tactic to hinder the recovery of its dues. The stock finally recovered some losses to settle at Rs 455, dropping by Rs 5.75 or 1.25%.
Image Source: iStock
Shares of airport services aggregator Dreamfolks Services hit their 5% lower circuit to close at Rs 131.07 on the NSE, after the company announced it has exited the domestic airport lounges business with immediate effect.
Image Source: iStock
The shares of One Mobikwik Systems finished at Rs 297.18, declining by Rs 14.20 or 4.56% after reports that the digital payments company lost around Rs 40 crore in a suspected fraud triggered by a system glitch earlier this month. Times of India reports said around Rs 40 crore were allegedly siphoned off over September 11 and 12 through a blitz of UPI transactions that bypassed the company’s balance checks.
Image Source: iStock
