Urban Company IPO jumps 57.5% on market debut, lists at ₹162.25 The IPO, which attracted bids worth ₹1.14 lakh crore, has been the most sought-after new listing in India this yeay By  Reuters Updated - September 17, 2025  at 10:28 AM. × Share WhatsApp X Facebook LinkedIn Messenger Reddit Mail https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/stock-markets/urban-company-ipo-jumps-575-on-market-debut-lists-at-16225/article70059783.ece Copy | Photo Credit:
											ANUSHREE FADNAVIS Shares of Indian home services platform Urban Company jumped 57.5% in pre-open trade on Wednesday, after its initial public offering drew bids worth 1.14 trillion rupees ($12.97 billion). The stock listed at 162.25 rupees on the National Stock Exchange of India, compared with its issue price of 103 rupees. Comments Published on  September 17, 2025 READ MORE THIS AD SUPPORTS OUR JOURNALISM. SUBSCRIBE FOR MINIMAL ADS. THIS AD SUPPORTS OUR JOURNALISM. SUBSCRIBE FOR MINIMAL ADS. THIS AD SUPPORTS OUR JOURNALISM. SUBSCRIBE FOR MINIMAL ADS.

