Title   : Prestige Estates shares rise 2%, extend gains to 3rd session as Nomura initiates coverage with buy rating 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-17T08:28:27
Fetched : 2025-09-17T13:20:43.694869
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/prestige-estates-shares-rise-2-extend-gains-to-3rd-session-as-nomura-initiates-coverage-with-buy-rating/articleshow/123939722.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The brokerage expects the Bengaluru-based developer to benefit from its rapid pan-India expansion, particularly in Mumbai and the National Capital Region, where it has scaled up both township and luxury projects. Nomura forecasts pre-sales of about Rs 2,90,000 crore in FY26, 10% higher than the company’s guidance of Rs 2,50,000–2,70,000 crore. Prestige logged pre-sales of Rs 1,21,000 crore in the June quarter and has launches worth Rs 2,99,000 crore lined up for the rest of the year.
Also read: Rs 14 crore to Rs 390 crore! Facebook's early investor strikes gold again, this time with Urban Company IPO
Nomura also highlighted Prestige’s strong execution track record, which should help scale up annuity and hotel earnings 4–5 times over the next four to five years. Exit rentals from commercial assets are expected to grow from Rs 820 crore in FY26 to nearly Rs 3,850 crore by FY30, driven by projects in Mumbai’s Bandra-Kurla Complex and Mahalaxmi. In hospitality, room capacity is set to double to around 2,400 keys by FY27 as new assets in Delhi Aerocity come onstream.
The brokerage noted that despite Prestige’s expansion and growth prospects, its valuation premium of about 40% to net asset value remains lower than Godrej Properties’ 108%. Key risks, however, include a slowdown in the Bengaluru real estate market and weaker-than-expected leasing in annuity assets.
Last month, the real estate developer reported a 26% year-on-year increase in consolidated net profit to Rs 292.5 crore for the June quarter, supported by higher revenue and robust housing demand. The company had posted a net profit of Rs 232.6 crore in the same period last year.
Total income rose to Rs 2,468.7 crore in Q1 FY26, up from Rs 2,024.5 crore in the year-ago period, according to a regulatory filing.
Read more: Dev Accelerator shares jump 5% after flat debut at IPO price. Should you buy, sell, or hold?
At about 1 pm, shares of the company were trading at Rs 1,653, higher by 1.7% from the last close on the NSE. Prestige Estates Projects shares have risen 50% in the last 6 months.
